During the ASEAN leaders' summit, Vice President Kamala Harris addressed the urgent issue of climate change. She highlighted the devastating impact of the climate crisis on Southeast Asia, including rising sea levels, typhoons, floods, and droughts. Harris also acknowledged that the United States has experienced its own share of climate-related disasters, such as wildfires and hurricanes. However, she emphasized that there are solutions available to combat climate change and create economic growth. The United States has launched several initiatives at the summit, including mobilizing funding for clean energy and climate-smart infrastructure, establishing partnerships on sustainable transportation and forest conservation, and sharing satellite data to help ASEAN nations prepare for extreme weather events. Harris stressed the interconnectedness of the world and the need for global cooperation to address the climate crisis. The conversation during the summit focused on galvanizing global action and working together to tackle climate challenges.